    "body": "@alcuadrado thanks for the link. what I paste above is [geth's client side code](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/efee85378ef426ab1dffa2e9045a60ea411415e1/ethclient/ethclient.go#L351), not server side code. so it will send the key as hash with leading zeros. And I tried and found the geth server node will accept two forms of data.\r\n\r\nBut the eips also have some inconsistencies , like the [eth_getproof](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/5b9685bb9c7ba0f5f921e4d3f23504f7ef08d5b1/EIPS/eip-1186.md#eth_getproof) api take the keys as 32bytes hash. \r\n\r\nIt is up to you to remove the restriction or just close this.",
